oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Discussion - Kingston Springs Suite - 2015-06-06
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Panel discussion: God Save Kingston Springs! Cash, Kris, Cowboy, Shel, and the Great Train Wreck of 1973 from the Ford Theater at the Country Music Hall of Fame and Museum on June 6, 2015. In support of the exhibit Dylan, Cash, and the Nashville Cats: A New Music City.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Jim Casey; Chris Gantry; Danny Flowers; Frye Gaillard;
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: Discussion hosted by Peter Cooper. Stories and legends of songwriter Vince Matthews and behind the scenes writing and recording of this musical work which was recorded in 1972 and released in 2015. Panelist include Jim Casey; Chris Gantry; Danny Flowers; Frye Gaillard. Includes audio from video and selected recorded audio excerpts. Performances include; Laid Back Country Picker -- Vince -- Floatin'.
